description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at Northamptonshire Healthcare NHS Foundation Trust. We are looking for highly motivated individuals to join our enthusiastic teams and support our clients with all activities of daily living.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1 Willow Close is a 6 bedded unit providing short breaks for adults with a learning disability who also have complex physical health care needs requiring specialist healthcare intervention. The service operates on a 24 hour rotational shift pattern inclusive of weekends and bank holidays as per rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have a passion for providing a quality service for people with complex needs and demonstrate an understanding of their needs and the needs of their families. You must want to make a positive difference to the lives of the people you care for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Under the supervision of a nurse you will participate in providing Short Breaks for clients with complex disabilities through a health care model. Working within the requirements of the policies and guidelines of the service, ensure that the clients are supported and assisted with all aspects of daily living, meeting their identified health needs and facilitating an individualised approach to leisure and activities. The post holder will be expected to work within the limits of their own competence, responsibility and accountability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you a challenging but rewarding environment with a dedicated and supportive staff team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust places an emphasis on staff development, supervision and appraisal and provides a full induction and/or preceptorship programme for all new staff and further training and developmental opportunities are available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to be a well-motivated individual who possesses good communication skills, is willing to learn and develop the skills and knowledge to support people with learning disabilities and complex health needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Duties will include taking part in day-to-day activities and household tasks. You will support clients with social activities and to access day care provision as well as engaging in activities within the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible rostering is offered and you will receive ongoing training, support and opportunities to develop your skills. The service operates 24/7, staff therefore work the full range of shift patterns including days, weekends, night shifts and Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For further details please contact Rachael Wye on 01604 588657 or rachael.wye@nhft.nhs.uk&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
